node.text:
At 140 years old at the time of the American Revolution, Harvard—and members of the Harvard community—played an important role in the country’s early history.⠀
⠀
This engraving by Paul Revere, created about 10 years before the American Revolution, is among the earliest representations of Harvard University, and is part of the Harvard Archives. Learn more about Harvard and the American Revolution in our Story.⠀
⠀
Image: Revere, P., & Chadwick, J. (1767). Westerly View of the Colledges in Cambridge, New England, 1767.

node.text:
Harvard Library's project to digitize its archives related to colonial North America began 10 years ago. More than 700,000 pages of material, from the somewhat mundane to documents related to well-known historical figures, are now much more easily accessible. Harvard curators argue that free, digital collections like this provide a chance to change how we think, learn, and teach when it comes to colonial North America. See our Story for more details.⠀

#Harvard 
⠀
Photo: @stephanie_blair_mitchell/Harvard Staff Photographer

node.text:
“Getting involved with the LGBTQ Policy Journal at the Harvard Kennedy School connected me to other LGBTQ policy leaders within Harvard and around the world! The 2020 Editors-in-Chief, Kamille and Elizabeth, welcomed me warmly, and our entire team is fantastic. This past year, it was especially important to have a tight-knit queer community I could turn to. Having pride is raw and revolutionary. LGBTQ friends, WE are raw and revolutionary. I’m sending a hug through time to 2012 me. Your 2021 self is PROUD of you!” - Marty Amaya, Harvard Kennedy School ’22

#Pride #PrideMonth #Harvard

node.accessibility_caption: A man wearing a suit and tie stands outside

node.text:
"I was pretty nervous about starting over again by coming to Harvard, especially as an LGBTQ+ person. What if I didn't find 'my people'? I'm happy to say that I did! Both members of the Harvard LGBTQ+ community and allies alike have made me feel at home and comfortable being my true self." - Alex Furleigh, Harvard Business School '22⠀
⠀
#Pride #PrideMonth #Harvard
